Note:
OpenBSD ARM64 (AArch64) Syscall Platform

Defines all OpenBSD ARM64 system call numbers, platform metadata, and
registration logic for the Runa compiler's syscall subsystem.

System call numbers on OpenBSD ARM64 are identical to OpenBSD x86_64 as OpenBSD
maintains a unified syscall numbering scheme across architectures.

The OpenBSD ARM64 calling convention is:
- X8 holds the syscall number
- Arguments passed in X0-X5 (up to 6 arguments)
- Return value in X0
- Syscall invoked via "svc #0"

OpenBSD ARM64 does not use the carry flag for error signaling on ARM64 in the
same way as x86_64. Instead, errors are indicated by a negative return value
similar to Linux ARM64 convention.

This file provides:
1. All OpenBSD ARM64 syscall number constants used by the compiler
2. Platform info creation for OpenBSD ARM64
3. Full syscall registration with argument types and categories
4. Fast name-to-number lookup without requiring a registry instance
:End Note

Import "compiler/backend/syscalls/platforms/platform_interface.runa" as PlatformInterface
Import "compiler/backend/syscalls/syscall_registry.runa" as SyscallRegistry
Import "compiler/backend/machine_code/common/machine_code_interface.runa" as MachineCode
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Layout
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/list.runa" as List

Note: ============================================================================
Note: OpenBSD ARM64 Syscall Number Constants
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
OpenBSD maintains unified syscall numbers across all architectures. The ARM64
syscall numbers are identical to the x86_64 numbers from sys/kern/syscalls.master.
This architectural uniformity simplifies cross-compilation within OpenBSD targets.

The calling convention differs (X8/X0-X5/svc #0 vs RAX/RDI-R9/syscall) but the
syscall numbers themselves are the same.
@End Reasoning

Note: --- File I/O Syscalls ---
Constant SYS_OBSD_ARM64_READ as Integer is 3
Constant SYS_OBSD_ARM64_WRITE as Integer is 4
Constant SYS_OBSD_ARM64_OPEN as Integer is 5
Constant SYS_OBSD_ARM64_CLOSE as Integer is 6
Constant SYS_OBSD_ARM64_FSTAT as Integer is 53
Constant SYS_OBSD_ARM64_LSEEK as Integer is 199
Constant SYS_OBSD_ARM64_IOCTL as Integer is 54
Constant SYS_OBSD_ARM64_OPENAT as Integer is 321

Note: --- Memory Management Syscalls ---
Constant SYS_OBSD_ARM64_MMAP as Integer is 197
Constant SYS_OBSD_ARM64_MUNMAP as Integer is 73
Constant SYS_OBSD_ARM64_BREAK as Integer is 17

Note: --- Process Management Syscalls ---
Constant SYS_OBSD_ARM64_EXIT as Integer is 1

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Total syscall count for registration validation
Note: ============================================================================
Constant OPENBSD_ARM64_SYSCALL_COUNT as Integer is 12

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Platform Info Creation
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Creates the PlatformInfo descriptor for OpenBSD ARM64. OpenBSD on AArch64 uses:
- Pointer size: 8 bytes (64-bit addressing)
- Endianness: little-endian (AArch64 defaults to little-endian on OpenBSD)
- Syscall instruction: "svc #0" (supervisor call)
- ABI: OpenBSD AAPCS64 (ARM AAPCS64 variant)

The platform_id of 11 (PLATFORM_OPENBSD_ARM64) identifies this target.
@End Reasoning

Process called "create_openbsd_arm64_platform_info" returns Integer:
    Note: Creates and returns a PlatformInfo struct for OpenBSD ARM64
    Note: Returns pointer to PlatformInfo, or 0 on allocation failure

    Let info be PlatformInterface.create_platform_info(PlatformInterface.PLATFORM_OPENBSD_ARM64, MachineCode.TARGET_ARCH_AARCH64, MachineCode.TARGET_OS_OPENBSD, 8, PlatformInterface.ENDIAN_LITTLE)
    If info is 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    PlatformInterface.platform_info_set_name(info, "OpenBSD ARM64")
    PlatformInterface.platform_info_set_abi(info, "OpenBSD AAPCS64")

    Return info
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Syscall Registration
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Registers all OpenBSD ARM64 syscall definitions with the central registry. The
syscall numbers are identical to OpenBSD x86_64 but the calling convention uses
ARM64 registers (X8 for number, X0-X5 for arguments, svc #0 for invocation).
@End Reasoning

Process called "register_openbsd_arm64_syscalls" that takes registry as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Registers all OpenBSD ARM64 syscall definitions with the given registry
    Note: Returns 1 on success, 0 on failure

    If registry is 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Create and register the platform info
    Let platform_info be create_openbsd_arm64_platform_info()
    If platform_info is 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let reg_result be SyscallRegistry.registry_register_platform(registry, PlatformInterface.PLATFORM_OPENBSD_ARM64, platform_info)
    If reg_result is 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Create and register the syscall calling convention
    Let convention be PlatformInterface.create_syscall_convention(PlatformInterface.PLATFORM_OPENBSD_ARM64)
    If convention is 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let conv_result be SyscallRegistry.register_convention(registry, PlatformInterface.PLATFORM_OPENBSD_ARM64, convention)
    If conv_result is 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Local alias for the platform ID to reduce verbosity
    Let pid be PlatformInterface.PLATFORM_OPENBSD_ARM64

    Note: ====================================================================
    Note: FILE I/O SYSCALLS
    Note: ====================================================================

    Note: --- read(fd, buf, count) -> ssize_t ---
    Let def_read be PlatformInterface.create_syscall_definition(SYS_OBSD_ARM64_READ, "read", 3, PlatformInterface.SYSCALL_CAT_FILE_IO, pid)
    PlatformInterface.syscall_def_set_arg_type(def_read, 0, PlatformInterface.SYSCALL_ARG_FD)
    PlatformInterface.syscall_def_set_arg_type(def_read, 1, PlatformInterface.SYSCALL_ARG_PTR)
    PlatformInterface.syscall_def_set_arg_type(def_read, 2, PlatformInterface.SYSCALL_ARG_SIZE)
    SyscallRegistry.register_syscall(registry, pid, def_read)

    Note: --- write(fd, buf, count) -> ssize_t ---
    Let def_write be PlatformInterface.create_syscall_definition(SYS_OBSD_ARM64_WRITE, "write", 3, PlatformInterface.SYSCALL_CAT_FILE_IO, pid)
    PlatformInterface.syscall_def_set_arg_type(def_write, 0, PlatformInterface.SYSCALL_ARG_FD)
    PlatformInterface.syscall_def_set_arg_type(def_write, 1, PlatformInterface.SYSCALL_ARG_PTR)
    PlatformInterface.syscall_def_set_arg_type(def_write, 2, PlatformInterface.SYSCALL_ARG_SIZE)
    SyscallRegistry.register_syscall(registry, pid, def_write)

    Note: --- open(pathname, flags, mode) -> fd ---
    Let def_open be PlatformInterface.create_syscall_definition(SYS_OBSD_ARM64_OPEN, "open", 3, PlatformInterface.SYSCALL_CAT_FILE_IO, pid)
    PlatformInterface.syscall_def_set_arg_type(def_open, 0, PlatformInterface.SYSCALL_ARG_PTR)
    PlatformInterface.syscall_def_set_arg_type(def_open, 1, PlatformInterface.SYSCALL_ARG_FLAGS)
    PlatformInterface.syscall_def_set_arg_type(def_open, 2, PlatformInterface.SYSCALL_ARG_MODE)
    SyscallRegistry.register_syscall(registry, pid, def_open)

    Note: --- close(fd) -> int ---
    Let def_close be PlatformInterface.create_syscall_definition(SYS_OBSD_ARM64_CLOSE, "close", 1, PlatformInterface.SYSCALL_CAT_FILE_IO, pid)
    PlatformInterface.syscall_def_set_arg_type(def_close, 0, PlatformInterface.SYSCALL_ARG_FD)
    SyscallRegistry.register_syscall(registry, pid, def_close)

    Note: --- fstat(fd, statbuf) -> int ---
    Let def_fstat be PlatformInterface.create_syscall_definition(SYS_OBSD_ARM64_FSTAT, "fstat", 2, PlatformInterface.SYSCALL_CAT_FILE_IO, pid)
    PlatformInterface.syscall_def_set_arg_type(def_fstat, 0, PlatformInterface.SYSCALL_ARG_FD)
    PlatformInterface.syscall_def_set_arg_type(def_fstat, 1, PlatformInterface.SYSCALL_ARG_PTR)
    SyscallRegistry.register_syscall(registry, pid, def_fstat)

    Note: --- lseek(fd, offset, whence) -> off_t ---
    Let def_lseek be PlatformInterface.create_syscall_definition(SYS_OBSD_ARM64_LSEEK, "lseek", 3, PlatformInterface.SYSCALL_CAT_FILE_IO, pid)
    PlatformInterface.syscall_def_set_arg_type(def_lseek, 0, PlatformInterface.SYSCALL_ARG_FD)
    PlatformInterface.syscall_def_set_arg_type(def_lseek, 1, PlatformInterface.SYSCALL_ARG_OFFSET)
    PlatformInterface.syscall_def_set_arg_type(def_lseek, 2, PlatformInterface.SYSCALL_ARG_INT)
    SyscallRegistry.register_syscall(registry, pid, def_lseek)

    Note: --- ioctl(fd, request, arg) -> int ---
    Let def_ioctl be PlatformInterface.create_syscall_definition(SYS_OBSD_ARM64_IOCTL, "ioctl", 3, PlatformInterface.SYSCALL_CAT_FILE_IO, pid)
    PlatformInterface.syscall_def_set_arg_type(def_ioctl, 0, PlatformInterface.SYSCALL_ARG_FD)
    PlatformInterface.syscall_def_set_arg_type(def_ioctl, 1, PlatformInterface.SYSCALL_ARG_UINT)
    PlatformInterface.syscall_def_set_arg_type(def_ioctl, 2, PlatformInterface.SYSCALL_ARG_PTR)
    SyscallRegistry.register_syscall(registry, pid, def_ioctl)

    Note: --- openat(dirfd, pathname, flags, mode) -> fd ---
    Let def_openat be PlatformInterface.create_syscall_definition(SYS_OBSD_ARM64_OPENAT, "openat", 4, PlatformInterface.SYSCALL_CAT_FILE_IO, pid)
    PlatformInterface.syscall_def_set_arg_type(def_openat, 0, PlatformInterface.SYSCALL_ARG_FD)
    PlatformInterface.syscall_def_set_arg_type(def_openat, 1, PlatformInterface.SYSCALL_ARG_PTR)
    PlatformInterface.syscall_def_set_arg_type(def_openat, 2, PlatformInterface.SYSCALL_ARG_FLAGS)
    PlatformInterface.syscall_def_set_arg_type(def_openat, 3, PlatformInterface.SYSCALL_ARG_MODE)
    SyscallRegistry.register_syscall(registry, pid, def_openat)

    Note: ====================================================================
    Note: MEMORY MANAGEMENT SYSCALLS
    Note: ====================================================================

    Note: --- mmap(addr, length, prot, flags, fd, offset) -> ptr ---
    Let def_mmap be PlatformInterface.create_syscall_definition(SYS_OBSD_ARM64_MMAP, "mmap", 6, PlatformInterface.SYSCALL_CAT_MEMORY, pid)
    PlatformInterface.syscall_def_set_arg_type(def_mmap, 0, PlatformInterface.SYSCALL_ARG_PTR)
    PlatformInterface.syscall_def_set_arg_type(def_mmap, 1, PlatformInterface.SYSCALL_ARG_SIZE)
    PlatformInterface.syscall_def_set_arg_type(def_mmap, 2, PlatformInterface.SYSCALL_ARG_FLAGS)
    PlatformInterface.syscall_def_set_arg_type(def_mmap, 3, PlatformInterface.SYSCALL_ARG_FLAGS)
    PlatformInterface.syscall_def_set_arg_type(def_mmap, 4, PlatformInterface.SYSCALL_ARG_FD)
    PlatformInterface.syscall_def_set_arg_type(def_mmap, 5, PlatformInterface.SYSCALL_ARG_OFFSET)
    SyscallRegistry.register_syscall(registry, pid, def_mmap)

    Note: --- munmap(addr, length) -> int ---
    Let def_munmap be PlatformInterface.create_syscall_definition(SYS_OBSD_ARM64_MUNMAP, "munmap", 2, PlatformInterface.SYSCALL_CAT_MEMORY, pid)
    PlatformInterface.syscall_def_set_arg_type(def_munmap, 0, PlatformInterface.SYSCALL_ARG_PTR)
    PlatformInterface.syscall_def_set_arg_type(def_munmap, 1, PlatformInterface.SYSCALL_ARG_SIZE)
    SyscallRegistry.register_syscall(registry, pid, def_munmap)

    Note: --- brk/break(addr) -> ptr ---
    Note: OpenBSD calls this "break" (syscall 17), registered under canonical name "brk"
    Let def_brk be PlatformInterface.create_syscall_definition(SYS_OBSD_ARM64_BREAK, "brk", 1, PlatformInterface.SYSCALL_CAT_MEMORY, pid)
    PlatformInterface.syscall_def_set_arg_type(def_brk, 0, PlatformInterface.SYSCALL_ARG_PTR)
    SyscallRegistry.register_syscall(registry, pid, def_brk)

    Note: ====================================================================
    Note: PROCESS MANAGEMENT SYSCALLS
    Note: ====================================================================

    Note: --- exit(status) -> noreturn ---
    Let def_exit be PlatformInterface.create_syscall_definition(SYS_OBSD_ARM64_EXIT, "exit", 1, PlatformInterface.SYSCALL_CAT_PROCESS, pid)
    PlatformInterface.syscall_def_set_arg_type(def_exit, 0, PlatformInterface.SYSCALL_ARG_INT)
    PlatformInterface.syscall_def_set_noreturn(def_exit)
    SyscallRegistry.register_syscall(registry, pid, def_exit)

    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Fast Name-to-Number Lookup (Registry-Free)
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Provides a direct name-to-syscall-number lookup for OpenBSD ARM64 without requiring
a registry instance. Since OpenBSD uses unified syscall numbers across architectures,
the numbers returned here are identical to OpenBSD x86_64.

Returns the syscall number if the name matches a known OpenBSD ARM64 syscall,
or -1 if the name is not recognized.
@End Reasoning

Process called "get_openbsd_arm64_syscall_number" that takes name as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Returns the syscall number for the given name string on OpenBSD ARM64
    Note: Returns -1 if the name is not a recognized syscall

    If name is 0:
        Return -1
    End If

    Let first_byte be __load_byte(name, 0)

    Note: --- Names starting with 'w' (write) ---
    If first_byte is 119:
        If __load_byte(name, 1) is 114:
            If __load_byte(name, 2) is 105:
                If __load_byte(name, 3) is 116:
                    If __load_byte(name, 4) is 101:
                        If __load_byte(name, 5) is 0:
                            Return SYS_OBSD_ARM64_WRITE
                        End If
                    End If
                End If
            End If
        End If
        Return -1
    End If

    Note: --- Names starting with 'r' (read) ---
    If first_byte is 114:
        If __load_byte(name, 1) is 101:
            If __load_byte(name, 2) is 97:
                If __load_byte(name, 3) is 100:
                    If __load_byte(name, 4) is 0:
                        Return SYS_OBSD_ARM64_READ
                    End If
                End If
            End If
        End If
        Return -1
    End If

    Note: --- Names starting with 'e' (exit) ---
    If first_byte is 101:
        If __load_byte(name, 1) is 120:
            If __load_byte(name, 2) is 105:
                If __load_byte(name, 3) is 116:
                    If __load_byte(name, 4) is 0:
                        Return SYS_OBSD_ARM64_EXIT
                    End If
                End If
            End If
        End If
        Return -1
    End If

    Note: --- Names starting with 'o' (open, openat) ---
    If first_byte is 111:
        If __load_byte(name, 1) is 112:
            If __load_byte(name, 2) is 101:
                If __load_byte(name, 3) is 110:
                    If __load_byte(name, 4) is 0:
                        Return SYS_OBSD_ARM64_OPEN
                    End If
                    If __load_byte(name, 4) is 97:
                        If __load_byte(name, 5) is 116:
                            If __load_byte(name, 6) is 0:
                                Return SYS_OBSD_ARM64_OPENAT
                            End If
                        End If
                    End If
                End If
            End If
        End If
        Return -1
    End If

    Note: --- Names starting with 'c' (close) ---
    If first_byte is 99:
        If __load_byte(name, 1) is 108:
            If __load_byte(name, 2) is 111:
                If __load_byte(name, 3) is 115:
                    If __load_byte(name, 4) is 101:
                        If __load_byte(name, 5) is 0:
                            Return SYS_OBSD_ARM64_CLOSE
                        End If
                    End If
                End If
            End If
        End If
        Return -1
    End If

    Note: --- Names starting with 'm' (mmap, munmap) ---
    If first_byte is 109:
        Let second_byte be __load_byte(name, 1)
        If second_byte is 109:
            If __load_byte(name, 2) is 97:
                If __load_byte(name, 3) is 112:
                    If __load_byte(name, 4) is 0:
                        Return SYS_OBSD_ARM64_MMAP
                    End If
                End If
            End If
        End If
        If second_byte is 117:
            If __load_byte(name, 2) is 110:
                If __load_byte(name, 3) is 109:
                    If __load_byte(name, 4) is 97:
                        If __load_byte(name, 5) is 112:
                            If __load_byte(name, 6) is 0:
                                Return SYS_OBSD_ARM64_MUNMAP
                            End If
                        End If
                    End If
                End If
            End If
        End If
        Return -1
    End If

    Note: --- Names starting with 'b' (brk) ---
    If first_byte is 98:
        If __load_byte(name, 1) is 114:
            If __load_byte(name, 2) is 107:
                If __load_byte(name, 3) is 0:
                    Return SYS_OBSD_ARM64_BREAK
                End If
            End If
        End If
        Return -1
    End If

    Note: --- Names starting with 'f' (fstat) ---
    If first_byte is 102:
        If __load_byte(name, 1) is 115:
            If __load_byte(name, 2) is 116:
                If __load_byte(name, 3) is 97:
                    If __load_byte(name, 4) is 116:
                        If __load_byte(name, 5) is 0:
                            Return SYS_OBSD_ARM64_FSTAT
                        End If
                    End If
                End If
            End If
        End If
        Return -1
    End If

    Note: --- Names starting with 'l' (lseek) ---
    If first_byte is 108:
        If __load_byte(name, 1) is 115:
            If __load_byte(name, 2) is 101:
                If __load_byte(name, 3) is 101:
                    If __load_byte(name, 4) is 107:
                        If __load_byte(name, 5) is 0:
                            Return SYS_OBSD_ARM64_LSEEK
                        End If
                    End If
                End If
            End If
        End If
        Return -1
    End If

    Note: --- Names starting with 'i' (ioctl) ---
    If first_byte is 105:
        If __load_byte(name, 1) is 111:
            If __load_byte(name, 2) is 99:
                If __load_byte(name, 3) is 116:
                    If __load_byte(name, 4) is 108:
                        If __load_byte(name, 5) is 0:
                            Return SYS_OBSD_ARM64_IOCTL
                        End If
                    End If
                End If
            End If
        End If
        Return -1
    End If

    Return -1
End Process
